\chapter{Technology Description}
Nowadays, with the rise of large language models such as ChatGPT, Microsoft's Copilot, Anthropic's Claude, and Meta's Llama. There is a wide use of this technology in area such as software development, higher education, K-12 education, grammer tools, and other helpful software that makes these mundane tasks relatively small and easy to do; and free up time to do other complex and time-consuming tasks.\\
However, this new technology for higher education and K-12 has been considered both a positive impact in education such as giving a helping hand with the instructor on teaching students concepts that they still don't understand via LLMs/chat-bots when the instructor is not available. Furthermore, it can become a negative impact in education such rampant cheating [academic dishonesty], doing the homework for you and not grapsing the concept fully; this could also lead to higher yield in procrastination\citep{abbas2024} which becomes yet another negative factor in one's individual education endevours.


